there was a period of time i did their jobs. good if u wanna achieve low mileage cos their delivery zones not too wide (depends on which hawker centre u go actually).so basically the consumer pays directly to whyQ for everything and thats where whyQ earns.Hokkien Meetakeaway at FC - $4order thru whyQ - $6.80If small order - got small order charge $1.50-$2 i thinkHawkers dont even need a machine to do this. the packer will be stationed at the FC  orders come in thru their phone app  go to the stall and manually order. They are given petty cash to pay for the food from the company. Once food is ready they bring all the food from the diff stalls back to the despatching table  that's where FP and LLM drivers come and collect (whyQ partner with FP so that there's greater outreach).There's cutoff time for the customer to order. Lunch is 11am 12pm 1pm. Dinner is 6pm 7pm 8pm. so the LLM orders will be despatched in the first half hour. If u see it despatched between :30 and :45  means late despatch or no rider take. sometimes no bike around they upgrade to car.The packers at the FC are paid $12/hr. 1030-1400 1730-2030.
so u add here and there  i really dont know how whyQ earns.
